portIssue!__\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">doElemReportIssue!__</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Reports an issue if `verbose` mode is enabled. ","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.doElemReportIssue!__","kind":"def","line":309,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.doElemReportIssue!__","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.lean#L309-L310"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.reportIssueIfVerbose\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">reportIssueIfVerbose</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">msg</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Message.html#Lean.MessageData\">MessageData</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.SymM\">SymM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Reports an issue if `verbose` mode is enabled. Does nothing if `verbose` is `false`. ","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.reportIssueIfVerbose","kind":"def","line":299,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.reportIssueIfVerbose","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.lean#L299-L302"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.reportIssue\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">reportIssue</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">msg</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Message.html#Lean.MessageData\">MessageData</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.SymM\">SymM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Adds an issue message to the issue tracker. ","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.reportIssue","kind":"def","line":293,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.reportIssue","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.lean#L293-L297"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.getConfig\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">getConfig</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.SymM\">SymM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Config\">Config</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.getConfig","kind":"def","line":290,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.getConfig","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.lean#L290-L291"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.isDebugEnabled\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">isDebugEnabled</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.SymM\">SymM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns `true` if `sym.debug` is set ","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.isDebugEnabled","kind":"def","line":286,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.isDebugEnabled","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.lean#L286-L288"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.share\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">share</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.SymM\">SymM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Incremental variant of `shareCommon` for expressions constructed from already-shared subterms.\n\nUse this when an expression `e` was produced by a Lean API (e.g., `inferType`, `mkApp4`) that\ndoes not preserve maximal sharing, but the inputs to that API were already maximally shared.\n\nUnlike `shareCommon`, this function does not use a local `Std.HashMap ExprPtr Expr` to\ntrack visited nodes. This is more efficient when the number of new (unshared) nodes is small,\nwhich is the common case when wrapping API calls that build a few constructor nodes around\nshared inputs.\n\nExample:\n```\n-- `a` and `b` are already maximally shared\nlet result := mkApp2 f a b  -- result is not maximally shared\nlet result ← shareCommonInc result -- efficiently restore sharing\n```\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.share","kind":"def","line":282,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.share","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.lean#L282-L284"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.shareCommonInc\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">shareCommonInc</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.SymM\">SymM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Incremental variant of `shareCommon` for expressions constructed from already-shared subterms.\n\nUse this when an expression `e` was produced by a Lean API (e.g., `inferType`, `mkApp4`) that\ndoes not preserve maximal sharing, but the inputs to that API were already maximally shared.\n\nUnlike `shareCommon`, this function does not use a local `Std.HashMap ExprPtr Expr` to\ntrack visited nodes. This is more efficient when the number of new (unshared) nodes is small,\nwhich is the common case when wrapping API calls that build a few constructor nodes around\nshared inputs.\n\nExample:\n```\n-- `a` and `b` are already maximally shared\nlet result := mkApp2 f a b  -- result is not maximally shared\nlet result ← shareCommonInc result -- efficiently restore sharing\n```\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.shareCommonInc","kind":"def","line":258,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.shareCommonInc","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.lean#L258-L280"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.shareCommon\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">shareCommon</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.SymM\">SymM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Applies hash-consing to `e`. Recall that all expressions in a `grind` goal have\nbeen hash-consed. We perform this step before we internalize expressions.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.shareCommon","kind":"def","line":248,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.shareCommon","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.lean#L248-L256"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.getIntExpr\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">getIntExpr</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.SymM\">SymM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the internalized `Int`.  ","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.getIntExpr","kind":"def","line":245,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.getIntExpr","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.lean#L245-L246"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.getOrderingEqExpr\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">getOrderingEqExpr</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.SymM\">SymM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the internalized `Ordering.eq`.  ","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.getOrderingEqExpr","kind":"def","line":243,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.getOrderingEqExpr","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.lean#L243-L244"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.getNatZeroExpr\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">getNatZeroExpr</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.SymM\">SymM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the internalized `0 : Nat` numeral.  ","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.getNatZeroExpr","kind":"def","line":241,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.getNatZeroExpr","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.lean#L241-L242"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/SymM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.isBoolFalseExpr\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</spa